The paper deals with the problem of distributed coordination of mobile robots, which is a common topic in the fields of multi-agent systems (cs.MA), robotics (cs.RO), and distributed computing (cs.DC). The algorithm presented in the paper involves ensuring that the robots are in general position, which is a concept from computational geometry (cs.CG) and is also relevant to robotics. The algorithm also involves collision-free motion, which is a common problem in robotics and control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents a distributed algorithm, which involves decision-making and communication among the robots, and thus may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
